A business robbery at a spa on the ground floor of a hotel in uMhlanga saw a young woman assaulted whilst the robbers fled with cash and cellphones, on Sunday evening. Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) Phoenix Operations Centre received a call from a bystander reporting a robbery in progress at a spa situated on the ground floor of the hotel and immediately, reaction officers were dispatched to the scene and upon arrival, found law enforcement agencies in attendance. <br />
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});<br /> “It is alleged that a red VW Golf 6 Gti with Gauteng registration plates was used as a getaway vehicle. The suspects’ vehicle was spotted travelling at high speed in the vicinity of the traffic circle outside McDonalds. The suspects fired shots after they noticed they were being pursued by reaction officers and other security officers. A high speed chase ensued, however, the suspects managed to evade arrest,” said Rusa head, Prem Balram. He said that reports from the scene indicate that two suspects entered the Spa Durban and held up staff while two of their accomplices kept watch on the outside. <br />
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});<br /> “One suspect was confirmed to be armed with a firearm while a second suspect was in possession of a knife.The suspects assaulted a 32-year-old employee who is four months pregnant and robbed her of an undisclosed amount of cash and cellphones. The robbers then exited the business and got into their getaway vehicle which was parked across the road. The employee was transported to hospital by ambulance for injuries she sustained during the robbery,” Balram added. Durban North SAPS communications officer, Captain Raymond Deokaran, said, “Police are investigating a business robbery case. The injured victim was highly traumatised. Four cellphones were taken together with an undislosed amount of cash.Police are viewing CCTV footage and investigations are ongoing.”